Rule: Higher education levels (Doctorate, Masters, Prof-school) increase the likelihood of earning more than $50k.
Occupations categorized as White-Collar, Professional, or Other/Unknown are associated with higher income potential.
Being Divorced may increase the likelihood of a higher income compared to being Married.
Working in Government or being Self-Employed is associated with higher income potential compared to working in the Private sector.
Being White instead of Other can be associated with higher income potential.
Gender being Male leads to higher income.
